Jan Siegmund

Corporate Vice President and Chief Financial Officer
Jan Siegmund was appointed Corporate Vice President and Chief Financial Officer in November, 2012.
Jan has been with ADP since June 1999, most recently as ADP's Chief Strategy Officer and President of the Added Value Services Division from 2007 to October 2012. As President of AVS, Jan was responsible for the AVS division, which included tax, compliance services and insurance. In addition, as Chief Strategy Officer, he had responsibility for ADP’s strategy, product management, marketing and corporate development.
Jan joined ADP as Vice President-Corporate Strategy. In 2000, he transferred to ADP's Brokerage Services Group as Senior Vice President for Strategy and Business Development. He later assumed the position of Corporate Vice President, leading ADP's Strategy, Marketing, Product Management, Government Affairs, and Corporate Development group. He has been instrumental in the development of ADP’s new growth strategy, which has resulted in the company's expansion into a number of important growth markets.
Prior to joining ADP, Jan spent six years with McKinsey and Company leading consulting engagements primarily in the financial services industry. He holds a doctor of philosophy degree in economics and a master of science degree in industrial engineering.






